input_str: Radiohead’s 20-year-old album OK Computer is back at the top of the U.K. chart as “the Glastonbury effect” again makes takes hold. The alternative-rock band leads Foo Fighters, Royal Blood, Stormzy and The xx, who also performed at this year’s festival and are enjoying big boosts as a result. Ed Sheeran can also be expected to see a sales advance, and not just in Britain: the world’s largest green-field music festival was broadcast live by BBC Worldwide.
